Me and my twin brother went to this pizzeria last year and the summer time.  Back in the '90s up until 1997,this pizzeria in my opinion was the best pizzeria in all of Brooklyn. The new owners today of this pizzeria is not the same owners as the owners in the '90s.  The dough tastes different, the cheese tastes different, and last but not least the sauce taste different.  I understand every pizzeria bakes their pizza different,but the pizza that's being made in this pizzeria is the worst.  Thin crust pizza is the best pizza to have, Pizza should never be doughy, The cheese should never be cheap, and the sauce should always have flavor.  wherever the owner is of this pizzeria, should learn a lot from Italians on how to big pizza, because the pizza that they're baking today is not pizza.
